61#define to_delayed_work linux_to_delayed_work
62
63struct workqueue_struct;
64
65struct work_struct {
66 volatile uintptr_t work_owner;
67 TAILQ_ENTRY(work_struct) work_entry;
68 void (*func)(struct work_struct *); /* Linux API name */
69};
70
71struct delayed_work {
72 struct work_struct work; /* Linux API name */
73 struct callout dw_callout;
74 TAILQ_ENTRY(delayed_work) dw_entry;
75 int dw_resched;
76 enum {
77 DELAYED_WORK_IDLE,
78 DELAYED_WORK_SCHEDULED,
79 DELAYED_WORK_RESCHEDULED,
80 DELAYED_WORK_CANCELLED,
81 } dw_state;
82};
83
84static inline struct delayed_work *
85to_delayed_work(struct work_struct *work)
86{
87 return container_of(work, struct delayed_work, work);
88}
89
90extern struct workqueue_struct *system_wq;
91extern struct workqueue_struct *system_long_wq;
92extern struct workqueue_struct *system_power_efficient_wq;

94int linux_workqueue_init(void);
95void linux_workqueue_fini(void);

97#define create_singlethread_workqueue(name) \
